#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &appname;"
msgstr "&appname; kasutamine"

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid "Quick Start"
msgstr "Kiirstart"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:7
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, &appname; starts with an empty book collection. To work with "
"some other type of collection, create it using the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>New</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item, or the button on the toolbar. Collections are "
"populated with some of the more common fields, but you can add, modify, or "
"delete them to suit your needs."
msgstr ""
"Vaikimisi käivitub &appname; tühja raamatukollektsiooniga. Mõnda muud laadi "
"kogu kasutamiseks loo see menüükäsuga <menuchoice><guimenu>Fail</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Uus</guimenuitem></menuchoice> või nupuga "
"tööriistaribal. Kogud täidetakse teatavate levinumate väljadega, kuid sa "
"võib neid lisada, muuta või kustutada just vastavalt oma vajadustele."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"New entries can be added by using the <link linkend=\"entry-editor"
"\"><interface>Entry Editor</interface></link>. The "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Collection</guimenu><guimenuitem>New Entry</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item will open the <interface>Entry Editor</"
"interface> with an empty entry ready for editing. The <interface>Entry "
"Editor</interface> can also be opened by using the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Show Entry Editor</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. Once you've entered the values for the "
"entry, you can save it to the collection by using the <guibutton>Save Entry</"
"guibutton> button in the <interface>Entry Editor</interface> dialog, which "
"remains open in case you want to continue adding new entries. Once you've "
"saved an entry in the collection, you can modify it by clicking on it in the "
"main window. If the <interface>Entry Editor</interface> is not already open, "
"you can double click an entry to open the editor and start editing."
msgstr ""
"Uusi kirjeid saab lisada <link linkend=\"entry-editor"
"\"><interface>kirjeredaktori</interface></link> abil. Menüükirje "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Kogu</guimenu><guimenuitem>Uus kirje</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> avab <interface>kirjeredaktori</interface> redigeerimisvalmi "
"tühja kirjega. <interface>Kirjeredaktori</interface> saab avada ka "
"menüükäsuga <menuchoice><guimenu>Seadistused</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Kirjeredaktori näitamine</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. "
"Kui oled sisestanud kirje väärtused, saad selle kogusse salvestada nupuga "
"<guibutton>Salvesta kirje</guibutton> <interface>kirjeredaktoris</"
"interface>, mis jääb avatuks, kui peaksid soovima veel kirjeid lisada. Kui "
"oled kirje kogusse salvestanud, võib seda edaspidi muuta sellel peaaknas "
"klõpsates. Kui <interface>kirjeredaktor</interface> pole veel avatud, võib "
"teha kirjel topeltklõpsu, mis avab redaktori ja võimaldab kirjet muutma "
"asuda."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to include an image in the entry, you can use the standard &kde; "
"File Selector by clicking the <guibutton>Select Image...</guibutton> button "
"in the <link linkend=\"entry-editor\"><interface>Entry Editor</interface></"
"link>, or you can drag an image from the file manager or web browser into "
"the <interface>Entry Editor</interface>."
msgstr ""
"Kui soovid kirjesse lisada pilti, saad kasutada tavapärast &kde; "
"failivalijat, kui klõpsad nupule <guibutton>Vali pilt...</guibutton> <link "
"linkend=\"entry-editor\"><interface>kirjeredaktoris</interface></link> või "
"lohistad pildi failihaldurist või veebibrauserist "
"<interface>kirjeredaktorisse</interface>."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you select an entry, the <link linkend=\"entry-view\"><interface>Entry "
"View</interface></link> shows a formatted view of the entry's contents. You "
"can change the template used for showing the entry in the <link linkend="
"\"configuration\"><interface>Configuration Dialog</interface></link>."
msgstr ""
"Kirje valimisel näitab <link linkend=\"entry-view"
"\"><interface>kirjeredaktor</interface></link> kirje sisu vormindatud kujul. "
"Kirje näitamiseks kasutatavat malli saab muuta <link linkend=\"configuration"
"\"><interface>seadistustedialoogis</interface></link>."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The entries in the collection are grouped together when they share the same "
"values for certain fields, such as the author or director. You can change "
"the field used for grouping by using the combo box in the toolbar or the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Group Selection</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Kogu kirjed rühmitatakse, kui neil on teatud väljadel ühine väärtus, näiteks "
"autor või lavastaja. Rühmitamiseks kasutatavat välja saab muuta liitkastis "
"tööriistaribal või menüükäsuga <menuchoice><guimenu>Seadistused</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Rühmitamisalus</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:27
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can use the <interface>Quick Filter</interface> in the toolbar to "
#| "quickly limit the visible entries to ones which contain the word you "
#| "type. The filter is also useful when you want to quickly find an entry. "
#| "You can type in the title or some other unique word that identifies the "
#| "entry and the <link linkend=\"detailed-view\"><interface>Column View</"
#| "interface></link> will only show the entries that match the filter. The "
#| "status bar shows you how many entries are in the collection, and how many "
#| "are currently being filtered."
msgid ""
"You can use the <interface>Quick Filter</interface> in the toolbar to limit "
"the visible entries. The filter is also useful when you want to quickly find "
"an entry. You can type in the title or some other unique word that "
"identifies the entry and the <link linkend=\"detailed-view"
"\"><interface>Column View</interface></link> will only show the entries that "
"match the filter. More complex filtering can use field names directly, such "
"as <emphasis>author=stephenson</emphasis>. The status bar shows you how many "
"entries are in the collection, and how many are currently being filtered."
msgstr ""
"Tööriistariba <interface>kiirfiltriga</interface> saab hõlpsasti piirata "
"nähtavaid kirjeid nendega, mis sisaldavad sinu kirjutatud sõna. Filter on "
"kasulik ka siis, kui tahad kiiresti mõnda kirjet leida. Võid kirjutada "
"näiteks pealkirja või mõne unikaalse sõna, mis kirje üheselt tuvastab, ning "
"<link linkend=\"detailed-view\"><interface>veeruvaade</interface></link> "
"näitabki ainult filtriga sobivaid kirjeid. Olekuriba näitab, kui palju "
"kirjeid on kogus ja kui paljud on parajasti filtreeritud."

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Usage"
msgstr "Üldine kasutamine"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main window has three distinct areas, all of which show information "
"about the collection in a different manner. The primary view is the <link "
"linkend=\"detailed-view\"><interface>Column View</interface></link> in the "
"upper right area, where the value of every field for each entry may be "
"shown. On the left side, tabs hold the <link linkend=\"group-view"
"\"><interface>Group View</interface></link>, which can be used to sort the "
"entries into groups in a tree-structure, the <link linkend=\"filter-view"
"\"><interface>Filter View</interface></link>, which is used to track which "
"entries meet certain criteria, and the <link linkend=\"loan-view"
"\"><interface>Loan View</interface></link>, where any loans are listed. "
"Finally, the <link linkend=\"entry-view\"><interface>Entry View</interface></"
"link> shows a formatted view of the data for a single entry, or an icon view "
"of a group of entries, in the lower right."
msgstr ""
"Peaaknal on kolm eristuvat osa, mis kõik näitavad eri viisil teavet kogu "
"kohta. Põhivaade on ülal paremal asuv <link linkend=\"detailed-view"
"\"><interface>veeruvaade</interface></link>, kus näeb iga kirje kõigi "
"väljade väärtusi. Vasakul on kaartidel <link linkend=\"group-view"
"\"><interface>rühmavaade</interface></link>, millega saab kirjeid rühmitada "
"puukujuliselt gruppidesse, <link linkend=\"filter-view"
"\"><interface>filtrivaade</interface></link>, mida saab kasutada teatavatele "
"tingimustele vastavate kirjete tuvastamiseks, ja <link linkend=\"loan-view"
"\"><interface>laenamisvaade</interface></link>, kus on kirjas kõik "
"laenutused. Lõpuks näitab <link linkend=\"entry-view"
"\"><interface>kirjevaade</interface></link> all paremal iga kirje andmete "
"vormindatud vaadet või kirjerühmade ikoonivaadet."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The &appname; Main Window</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&appname; peaaken</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The &appname; Main Window</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&appname; peaaken</phrase>"

#. Tag: interface
#: fundamentals.docbook:56
#, no-c-format
msgid "Column View"
msgstr "Veeruvaade"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any of the fields in the collections may be shown in the <interface>Column "
"View</interface>, although <emphasis><link linkend=\"para\">Paragraph</"
"link></emphasis>, <emphasis><link linkend=\"image\">Image</link></emphasis>, "
"and <emphasis><link linkend=\"table\">Table</link></emphasis> fields will "
"probably not be useful. Right-clicking on the header of the view opens a "
"menu for selecting the visible fields. The columns may be resized and "
"reordered in any way, and the settings will be saved between sessions."
msgstr ""
"Mis tahes kogu välju võib lasta näidata <interface>veeruvaates</interface>, "
"ehkki väljad <emphasis><link linkend=\"para\">Lõik</link></emphasis>, "
"<emphasis><link linkend=\"image\">Pilt</link></emphasis> ja <emphasis><link "
"linkend=\"table\">Tabel</link></emphasis> pole ehk kõige mõttekamad. "
"Paremklõpsuga vaate päisel saab avada menüü, mis võimaldab valida nähtavaid "
"välju. Veergude suurust ja paiknemist saab täiesti oma tahtmist mööda muuta, "
"kusjuures seadistused salvestatakse, nii et need kehtivad ka järgmise seansi "
"ajal."

#. Tag: interface
#: fundamentals.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Group View"
msgstr "Rühmavaade"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <interface>Group View</interface> groups the entries in a tree-view by "
"any field which <link linkend=\"field-options\">allows grouping</link>. The "
"number of entries in each group is shown next to the group name. Groups may "
"be expanded or collapsed by clicking the arrow sign, or by double-clicking "
"the item. Expanding and contracting all the groups are options in the right-"
"click context menu. The tree may be sorted either by the group name, or by "
"the count, by clicking on the header. A group may also be used as a filter "
"for the <link linkend=\"detailed-view\"><interface>Column View</interface></"
"link>, by right-clicking on the group item."
msgstr ""
"<interface>Rühmavaade</interface> rühmitab kirjed puukujuliselt mis tahes "
"välja jälgi, mis <link linkend=\"field-options\">võimaldab rühmitamist</"
"link>. Iga rühma kirjete arvu näeb rühma nime kõrval. Rühmi saab avada ja "
"sulgeda noolemärgile klõpsates või rühma nimel topeltklõpsu tehes. Kõigi "
"rühmade avamise ja sulgemise käsud leiab paremklõpsuga avanevast "
"kontekstimenüüst. Puud võib sortida ka rühma nime või kirjete arvu järgi, "
"klõpsates päisele. Rühma saab kasutada ka filtrina <link linkend=\"detailed-"
"view\"><interface>veeruvaate</interface></link> jaoks, milleks tuleb rühma "
"nimel teha paremklõps."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When more than one field in the collection has the <emphasis><link linkend="
"\"fields-dialog\"><guilabel>Format as a name</guilabel></link></emphasis> "
"option turned on, an additional group is added to combine all those fields "
"into one single <emphasis>People</emphasis> pseudo-group."
msgstr ""
"Kui enam kui ühel kogu välja puhul on valitud <emphasis><link linkend="
"\"fields-dialog\"><guilabel>Nimena vormindamine</guilabel></link></"
"emphasis>, lisatakse täiendavad rühmad, mis kombineerivad kõik need väljad "
"üheks pseudorühmaks <emphasis>Inimesed</emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If an entry does not contain a value for the field being used to form the "
"groups, it is placed in the <emphasis>(Empty)</emphasis> group, which uses a "
"red folder."
msgstr ""
"Kui kirjes puudub väärtus välja puhul, mida kasutatakse rühma "
"moodustamiseks, asetatakse see rühma <emphasis>(Tühi)</emphasis>, mida "
"tähistab punane kataloogiikoon."

#. Tag: interface
#: fundamentals.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "Filter View"
msgstr "Filtrivaade"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:83
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If any filters are saved for the collection, the <interface>Filter View</"
#| "interface> becomes active. As you add or modify entries, they will "
#| "automatically be checked against the filters and add or removed as "
#| "appropriate. The filter may be modified by double-clicking on the item to "
#| "open the <interface>Advanced Filter Dialog</interface>. Right-clicking "
#| "gives you the option to delete it altogether."
msgid ""
"If any filters are saved for the collection, the <interface>Filter View</"
"interface> becomes active. As you add or modify entries, they will "
"automatically be checked against the filters and add or removed as "
"appropriate. The filter may be modified by double-clicking on the item to "
"open the <link linkend=\"filter-dialog\"><interface>Advanced Filter Dialog</"
"interface></link>. Right-clicking gives you the option to delete it "
"altogether."
msgstr ""
"Kui kogusse on salvestatud filtreid, muutub aktiivseks ka "
"<interface>filtrivaade</interface>. Kirjeid lisades või muutes "
"kontrollitakse neid automaatselt filtrite suhtes ning vajaduse korral "
"lisatakse või eemaldatakse. Filtrit saab muuta, kui teha sellel topeltklõps, "
"mis avab <interface>täiustatud filtreerimise dialoogi</interface>. "
"Paremklõps annab võimaluse filter üldse kustutada."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The <interface>Filter View</interface></screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo><interface>Filtrivaade</interface></screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The <interface>Filter View</interface></phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase><interface>Filtrivaade</interface></phrase>"

#. Tag: interface
#: fundamentals.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loan View"
msgstr "Laenamisvaade"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once entries are checked-out on loan, the <interface>Loan View</interface> "
"is added to the window, so those borrowed entries may be tracked. Loans are "
"tracked on a per-entry bases, so right-clicking on an entry item has an "
"option for modifying the loan using the <interface>Loan Dialog</interface>."
msgstr ""
"Kui mõni kirje on märgitud väljalaenatuks, lisatakase aknasse "
"<interface>laenamisvaade</interface>, mis annab hea võimaluse jälgida "
"laenatud esemete saatust. Laenutusi jälgitakse kjrjepõhiselt, nii et "
"paremklõpsuga kirjel leiab ka võimaluse muuta laenutust "
"<interface>laenamisdialoogi</interface> vahendusel."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The <interface>Loan View</interface></screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo><interface>Laenamisvaade</interface></screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The <interface>Loan View</interface></phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase><interface>Laenamisvaade</interface></phrase>"

#. Tag: interface
#: fundamentals.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entry View"
msgstr "Kirjevaade"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A formatted representation of the entry's values is shown in the "
"<interface>Entry View</interface>. Templates are used for the layout and any "
"additional graphics. Separate templates for each type of collection may be "
"specified in the <link linkend=\"template-options\"><interface>Configuration "
"Dialog</interface></link>, along with custom colors and fonts."
msgstr ""
"Kirje väärtusi vormindatud kujul näeb <interface>kirjevaates</interface>. "
"Paigutuse ja graafika jaoks kasutatakse malle. Igale kogutüübile saab "
"määrata omaette malli konkreetsete värvide ja fontidega <link linkend="
"\"template-options\"><interface>seadistustedialoogis</interface></link>."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All of the default templates honor the color and font selection, but other "
"custom templates might not. The default templates also make &URL; fields "
"active, which will open up with the default &kde; file association. When "
"exporting to &HTML;, the current template is used for exporting the "
"individual entry files."
msgstr ""
"Kõik vaikemallid järgivad valitud värve ja fonte, kohandatud mallid aga seda "
"teha ei pruugi. Vaikemallides on ka aktiivsed &URL;-idega väljad, millele "
"klõpsamise järel avamisel kasutatakse &kde; vaikimisi failiseoseid. "
"Eksportimisel &HTML;-i kasutatakse konkreetsete kirjefailide ekspordil "
"parajasti aktiivset malli."

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Statusbar"
msgstr "Olekuriba"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The status bar is used to show you what &appname; is currently doing. It "
"also includes a total count of the entries in the collection, and if a "
"filter is being used, how many are currently visible."
msgstr ""
"Olekuribal näeb, mida &appname; parajasti teeb. Samuti on seal näha kogu "
"kirjete koguarv ja filtri kasutamise korral ka see, kui paljud kirjed on "
"parajasti näha."

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Entries"
msgstr "Kirjete muutmine"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> is used to add and modify entries in "
"the collection. Double-clicking on an entry in either the <interface>Group "
"View</interface> or the <interface>Column View</interface> opens the "
"<interface>Entry Editor</interface> with that entry. New entries may be "
"created using the <menuchoice><guimenu>Collection</guimenu></menuchoice> "
"menu, the toolbar icon, or the button in the <interface>Entry Editor</"
"interface> itself."
msgstr ""
"Kogu kirjete lisamiseks ja muutmiseks on mõeldud <interface>kirjeredaktor</"
"interface>. Topeltklõps mõnel kirjel <interface>rühmavaates</interface> või "
"<interface>veeruvaates</interface> avab vastava kirje "
"<interface>kirjeredaktoris</interface>. Uusi kirjeid saab luua kas menüü "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Kogu</guimenu></menuchoice>, tööriistariba ikooni või "
"nupu abil <interface>kirjeredaktoris</interface> endas."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Closing the <interface>Entry Editor</interface> when changes have been made "
"but not saved will cause a warning message to appear. The fields are grouped "
"by category and appear in the order that they appear in the <link linkend="
"\"fields-dialog\"><interface>Collection Fields Dialog</interface></link>. "
"They may also be reordered."
msgstr ""
"<interface>Kirjeredaktori</interface> sulgemisel, kui selles on tehtud "
"muudatusi, aga neid pole salvestatud, ilmub nähtavale hoiatus. Välju "
"rühmitatakse kategooriate kaupa ning nad on näha samas järjekorras, milles "
"nad esinevad <link linkend=\"fields-dialog\"><interface>kogu väljade "
"dialoogis</interface></link>. Neid saab küll ka ümber paigutada."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface></screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface></screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface></phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface></phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking the field title for a <link linkend=\"url\"><emphasis>&URL;</"
"emphasis></link> field will open the link using the default &kde; file "
"association. The <guiicon>&URL; selector</guiicon> button beside the text "
"entry will open the default &kde; File Open Dialog, but the field is not "
"limited to local files."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"url\"><emphasis>&URL;</emphasis></link>-välja puhul välja "
"nimel klõpsamine avab lingi &kde; vaikimisi failiseoseid kasutades. "
"<guiicon>&URL;-i valija</guiicon> nupp tekstikirje kõrval avab &kde; "
"vaikimisi faili avamise dialoogi, kuid see väli ei ole piiratud ainult "
"kohalike failidega."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For <link linkend=\"image\"><emphasis>Image</emphasis></link> fields, the "
"<guibutton>Select Image...</guibutton> button opens up the &kde; image file "
"selection dialog. The image is saved in the collection in the original "
"format, and a scaled version is shown in the <interface>Entry Editor</"
"interface>. The image may be cleared by using the <guibutton>Clear</"
"guibutton> button. Cleared images are removed from the collection."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"image\"><emphasis>Pildi</emphasis></link>välja puhul avab "
"nupp <guibutton>Vali pilt...</guibutton> &kde; pildifaili valimise dialoogi. "
"Pilt salvestatakse kogusse originaalvormingus ning selle skaleeritud "
"versiooni näeb <interface>kirjeredaktoris</interface>. Pildi saab kõrvaldada "
"nupuga <guibutton>Puhasta</guibutton>. Kõrvaldatud pildid eemaldatakse "
"kogust."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> for <emphasis>Image</"
"emphasis> fields</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""
"<screeninfo><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface> <emphasis>pildi</"
"emphasis>väljaga</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> for <emphasis>Image</"
"emphasis> fields</phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface> <emphasis>pildi</"
"emphasis>väljaga</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The edit widget also supports drag-and-drop. Dragging an image file from a "
"file-manager or browser window does the same thing as selecting the image in "
"the File Selector. Dragging an image from the edit widget into a &konqueror; "
"file manager window will save the image in that folder."
msgstr ""
"Redigeerimisvidin toetab ka lohistamist. Failivalija kasutamise asemel võib "
"sama hästi pildi kohale lohistada failihaldurist või brauseriaknast. Pildi "
"lohistamine redigeerimisvidinast &konqueror;i failihalduriaknasse salvestab "
"pildi kausta, kuhu see lohistati."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:178
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "By default, the images are stored in the collection data file, keeping "
#| "everything contained in one location. However, too many images will cause "
#| "&appname; to slow down significantly as well result in a very large data "
#| "file. Alternatively, &appname; can save the images separately, either in "
#| "the <filename class=\"directory\">$<envar>KDEHOME</envar>/share/apps/"
#| "tellico/data/</filename> folder or in a folder in the same location as "
#| "the data file. Loading and saving data files is much faster if images are "
#| "stored separately, but the data files are no longer portable or "
#| "archivable. Self-contained data files can always be created by using the "
#| "<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenu>Export</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Export to Zip...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu "
#| "item."
msgid ""
"By default, the images are stored in the collection data file, keeping "
"everything contained in one location. However, too many images will cause "
"&appname; to slow down significantly as well result in a very large data "
"file. Alternatively, &appname; can save the images separately, either in the "
"<filename class=\"directory\">~/.local/share/tellico/data/</filename> folder "
"or in a folder in the same location as the data file. Loading and saving "
"data files is much faster if images are stored separately, but the data "
"files are no longer portable or archivable. Self-contained data files can "
"always be created by using the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenu>Export</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export to Zip...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Vaikimisi salvestatakse pildid kogu andmefaili, mis hoiab kõike vajalikku "
"ühes kohas. Kuid liiga suur piltide hulk aeglustab märgatavalt &appname; "
"tööd ning tekitab mõistagi ka väga suure andmefaili. &appname; võib "
"seepärast salvestada pildid eraldi kas kataloogi <filename class=\"directory"
"\">$<envar>KDEHOME</envar>/share/apps/tellico/data/</filename> või kataloogi "
"samas kohas, kus asub andmefail. Andmefailide laadimine ja salvestamine on "
"palju kiirem, kui pildid on eraldi salvestatud, kuid andmed ei ole sel juhul "
"enam porditavad ega arhiveeritavad. Eneseküllaseid andmefaile saab alati "
"luua menüükäsuga <menuchoice><guimenu>Fail</guimenu><guimenu> Eksportimine</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Ekspordi Zip-ina...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"table\"><emphasis>Table</emphasis></link> fields begin with "
"five rows, but moving the cursor to the last row automatically adds another. "
"For multi-column tables, only the first column is used for grouping or "
"formatting."
msgstr ""
"Väljad <link linkend=\"table\"><emphasis>Tabel</emphasis></link> algavad "
"viie reaga, kuid kursori viimine viimasesse ritta lisab automaatselt uue "
"rea. Mitmeveerulise tabeli korral arvestatakse rühmitamisel või "
"vormindamisel ainult esimest veergu."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> for <emphasis>Table</"
"emphasis> fields</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""
"<screeninfo><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface> <emphasis>tabeli</"
"emphasis>väljaga</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> for <emphasis>Table</"
"emphasis> fields</phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface> <emphasis>tabeli</"
"emphasis>väljaga</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Multiple Entries"
msgstr "Mitme kirje muutmine"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multiple entries may be edited at the same time by selecting more than one "
"in either the <interface>Group View</interface> or the <interface>Column "
"View</interface>. If multiple entries are selected, the fields which contain "
"the same value in every entry are enabled. If entries have different values, "
"then the fields are disabled. Check boxes are added to the extreme right for "
"each field entry which control whether the field is enabled or not, as shown "
"in the screenshot below."
msgstr ""
"Mitut kirjet korraga saab muuta, kui valida rohkem kui üks kirje "
"<interface>rühmavaates</interface> või <interface>veeruvaates</interface>. "
"Mitme kirje valimisel on aktiveeritud väljad, mis sisaldavad kõigis kirjetes "
"ühesugust väärtust. Kui kirjetel on väärtused erinevad, on need välja "
"mitteaktiivsed. Iga väljakirje paremasse serva on lisatud märkekastid, "
"millega saab määrata, kas väli on aktiivne või mitte, nagu näha ka siinsel "
"pildil."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only enabled fields will be modified when the entries are saved, which makes "
"large-scale editing much easier. For example, to set the Medium of all the "
"video entries in the collection, make sure the Medium field is enabled. "
"Change it to <acronym>DVD</acronym>, then save the entries. Only the Medium "
"field will be modified, preserving all the other field values for the "
"entries."
msgstr ""
"Kirjete salvestamisel muudetakse ainult aktiivseid välju, mis muudab "
"ulatusliku redigeerimise palju hõlpsamaks. Näiteks selleks, et määrata "
"kõigile kogu videokirjetele andmekandja, tuleb muuta aktiivseks väli "
"Andmekandja. Anna väärtuseks <acronym>DVD</acronym> ja salvesta kirjed. "
"Muudetakse ainult välja Andmekandja, kõigi kirjete kõigi muude väljade "
"väärtused jäävad endiseks."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> for multiple entries</"
"screeninfo>"
msgstr ""
"<screeninfo><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface> mitme kirje korral</"
"screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> for multiple entries</phrase>"
msgstr ""
"<phrase><interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface> mitme kirje korral</phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:217
#, no-c-format
msgid "Updating Entry Data"
msgstr "Kirje andmete uuendamine"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Entries may be automatically updated by querying the data sources available "
"for the current collection type, which is very useful for combining "
"information from multiple sources. For example, you may add a movie to your "
"collection using the <link linkend=\"amazon-web-services\">Amazon.com Web "
"Services</link>, and then update the entry with additional information from "
"the <link linkend=\"imdb\">Internet Movie Database</link>."
msgstr ""
"Kirjeid saab automaatselt uuendada, kui esitada päring antud kogutüübi "
"korral saadaolevatele andmeallikatele, mis on kasulik mitme allika teabe "
"ühendamiseks. Nii võib näiteks lisada oma kogusse filmi <link linkend="
"\"amazon-web-services\">Amazon.com-i veebiteenuste</link> abil ning seejärel "
"uuendada kirjete lisateabega, mida pakub <link linkend=\"imdb\">Internet "
"Movie Database</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only empty fields are updated unless the <link linkend=\"data-sources-options"
"\">setting for that source</link> allows results to overwrite existing "
"information. For <link linkend=\"externalexec\">external scripts</link>, an "
"update field must be specified in the source options."
msgstr ""
"Uuendatakse ainult tühje välju, kui just <link linkend=\"data-sources-options"
"\">konkreetse allika seadistused</link> ei luba olemasolevat teavet üle "
"kirjutada. <link linkend=\"externalexec\">Välise skripti</link> korral peab "
"allika valikutes olema määratud uuendusväli."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The entry updating may be started via the right-click menu for an entry, or "
"by using the <menuchoice><guimenu>Collection</guimenu><guimenuitem>Update "
"Entry</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Kirjet saab uuendada kas paremklõpsuga kirjel avanevast menüüst või "
"menüükäsuga <menuchoice><guimenu>Kogu</guimenu><guimenuitem>Uuenda kirjet</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Fields"
msgstr "Väljade muutmine"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <interface>Collection Fields Dialog</interface> allows you to add new "
"fields to the collection, to modify the existing ones, or to delete fields "
"altogether."
msgstr ""
"<interface>Kogu väljade dialoogi</interface> võimaldab lisada kogusse uusi "
"välju, muuta olemasolevaid või neid hoopis kustutada."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: fundamentals.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<screeninfo>The &appname; <interface>Collection Fields Dialog</interface></"
"screeninfo>"
msgstr ""
"<screeninfo>&appname; <interface>kogu väljade dialoog</interface></"
"screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: fundamentals.docbook:247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>The &appname; <interface>Collection Fields Dialog</interface></"
"phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&appname; <interface>kogu väljade dialoog</interface></phrase>"

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid "Field List"
msgstr "Väljade loend"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the left side of the dialog is the list of the current fields. Modified "
"fields are shown in bold italics. The buttons below the list will add or "
"delete a field, and the arrows can be used to change their order. The order "
"of the fields in the list is important because the <interface>Entry Editor</"
"interface> uses the order for its layout. For each category, the fields will "
"be laid out from left to right, according to the top-to-bottom order of the "
"fields in the list."
msgstr ""
"Dialoogi vasakus servas on näha aktiivsete väljade loend. Muudetud välju "
"näidatakse rasvases kaldkirjas. Loendi all olevate nuppudega saab välju "
"lisada või kustutada, nooltega nende järjekorda muuta. Väljade järjekord "
"loendis on oluline, sest just seda järjekorda kasutab "
"<interface>kirjeredaktor</interface> oma paigutuse juures. Iga kategooria "
"korral paigutatakse väljad vasakult paremale vastavalt sellele, kuidas nad "
"esinevad loendis ülalt alla."

#. Tag: title
#: fundamentals.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "Field Properties"
msgstr "Välja omadused"

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A field is defined by its title, type, category, description, and possibly a "
"default value or some allowed values. The title is used everywhere to refer "
"to the field in the user interface. The <interface>Entry Editor</interface> "
"uses it to prompt for values. The <interface>Column View</interface> uses it "
"as a column header. The different types of fields are <link linkend=\"field-"
"types\">explained in the Field Types section</link>. The description is used "
"as a tooltip in the <interface>Entry Editor</interface>, perhaps to provide "
"an explanation of the field's contents. In addition, for <link linkend="
"\"derived\">fields with <emphasis>derived</emphasis> values</link>, a value "
"template is used to format the field's value. The default value is "
"automatically added when creating a new entry. The list of allowed values "
"for <link linkend=\"choice\"><emphasis>Choice</emphasis></link> fields "
"should be separated by a semi-colon."
msgstr ""
"Välja defineerib selle pealkiri, tüüp, kategooria, kirjeldus, samuti "
"vaikimisi väärtus või mitu lubatud väärtust. Pealkirja kasutatakse kogu "
"kasutajaliideses välja tähistamiseks. <interface>Kirjeredaktor</interface> "
"pruugib seda väärtuste jaoks. <interface>Veeruvaade</interface> tarvitab "
"seda veerupäisena. Väljade eri tüüpe selgitab <link linkend=\"field-types"
"\">väljatüüpide sektsioon</link>. Kirjeldust kasutatakse "
"<interface>kirjeredaktoris</interface> kohtspikrina, näiteks välja sisu "
"selgitamiseks. Lisaks kasutatakse <link linkend=\"derived"
"\"><emphasis>tuletatud</emphasis> väärtustega väljade</link> korral "
"väärtusemalli välja väärtuse vormindamiseks. Uue kirje loomisel lisatakse "
"automaatselt vaikeväärtus. Lubatud väärtuste loendis <link linkend=\"choice"
"\"><emphasis>valiku</emphasis></link>väljadel tuleb väärtuste eraldamiseks "
"tarvitada semikoolonit."

#. Tag: para
#: fundamentals.docbook:266
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"New fields may be any type, but changing the type of existing fields is "
"restricted to compatible types, as shown in the table below:"
msgstr ""
"Uued väljad võivad olla mis tahes tüüpi, kuid olemasolevate väljade tüübi "
"muutmisel saab kasutada ainult sobivaid tüüpe, nagu näha ka siinsel pildil."

